{
  "text": "Kim et al. evaluated parameters that predicted optimal lumbar lordosis and sagittal alignment in adult spinal deformity (ASD) patients fused from the thoracolumbar spine (T9-L2) to L5 or S1 [CITATION_1] . Patients with postoperative lumbar lordosis that exceeded thoracic kyphosis by 20",
